title: Idiot Threatens Judge Judy, Then Gets Stuck Inside Courtoom!
description:
Judge Judy lectures four men about gun ownership, who are being sued for shooting the Plaintiff's car with a gun.  After his stumpy friend gets thrown out of courtroom for trying to talk over Judge Judy, one idiot redneck subtly threaten's Judge Judy by saying, "You better watch him.  You never know what people'll do these days."  Judy rules against him, and asks Officer Bird to throw him out of the courtroom.  On his way out, Dummy gets stuck because he can't figure out whether to pull or push the doors.  "Push!" calls Bird.  Priceless!  Reminds me of this classic cartoon from "The Far Side."

title: Judge Judy Divorced Her Husband Immediately After This Happened
description:
Did you know that Judge Judy was the only woman in her class of 126 students at American University's Washington College of Law? Did you know that she and her husband Jerry divorced and remarried within just one year?

In this video, we delve into the fascinating personal life of Judith Sheindlin, better known as Judge Judy. We explore her rise to fame as a tough-talking judge, from her early days as a prosecutor in the New York family court system to becoming one of the most recognizable faces on daytime television. But beyond her professional success, we uncover the dramatic turn of events in her personal life that led to a swift divorce from her husband Jerry Sheindlin in 1990.

The video examines the impact of losing her father and how it strained her marriage, leading to their separation. We discuss the period of self-discovery that followed for both Judy and Jerry, and the surprising decision to remarry just a year later. Through their story, we explore valuable lessons about communication in relationships, the importance of personal growth, and the possibility of second chances in love.

We also share Judge Judy's recent insights on maintaining a long-lasting marriage, including her advice on personal space and continued attraction. This video offers a unique glimpse into the personal journey of one of television's most formidable personalities, demonstrating that even the toughest judges can face personal challenges and emerge stronger.

description:

The defendant is accused of failing to charge his ankle monitor, which is a violation of his bond conditions. title: Judge Judy interview on her Life and Career (2009)
description:
In her two-hour interview, Judge Judith Sheindlin discusses in detail her transition from being a New York Family Court judge to becoming a phenomenal television success as "Judge Judy." 
Check out these INSPIRING Judge Judy books on Amazon!
Keep It Simple, Stupid: https://geni.us/BFizc
Beauty Fades, Dumb Is Forever: https://geni.us/NAJr
You're Smarter Than You Look: https://geni.us/J3oU

She chronicles her rise to notoriety, which peaked when she was featured on 60 Minutes. From that appearance, she soon was offered the opportunity to bring her "no excuses" judicial philosophy to the small screen. Judge Sheindlin talks about Judge Judy's flawed pilot and how the show found its footing early-on. She also discusses her courtroom demeanor (including her famous "Judy-isms") and talks about the production details of the show.

title: Where is Judge Judy Now? (2024)
description:
Where is Judge Judy Now? (2024)
After 25 years on the air, Judy Sheindlin's hit series Judge Judy came to an end in May 2021. That November, she launched a new show, Judy Justice, on Freevee, Amazon's free premium streaming service, with new episodes airing every weekday. Many fans believe that the name is not the only thing that has changed about Judge Judy, but little else has changed. However, her new TV show aside, what else has been going on for Judge Judy?
